#X text 38 -74 Weighted random selection - using random and moses;
#X text 37 -56 A simple way to get a bunch of events with a certain
probability distribution is to generate uniformly distributed numbers
and stream them with moses.;
#X text 157 42 For example moses 10 sends integers greater than 9 to
its right outlet. A cascade of moses objects will distribute them in
a ratio over the combined outlets when the sum of all ratios equals
the range of random numbers. The outlets of moses 10 distribute the
numbers in the ratio 1 : 9 When the right outlet is further split by
moses 50 numbers in the range 0 to 100 are split in the ratio 10 :
40 : 50 \, and since the distribution of input numbers is uniform they
are sent to one of three outlets with 10% \, 40% and 50% probability.
;
